nodes.bodyText: also please move sqlParserOptions.useEnhancedErrorHandl... to before guice bind

is it avoidable?
i am concerned we could want to have dep the other way -- use testing goodies in toolkit's tests

don't configure SAC on worker
people know it's not required and they don't do this; so we shouldn't do this in tests either

It's neither "testing implementation of SystemAccessControl" nor "testing's utilities for SystemAccessControl" ...
I don't know what this class represents.
it may be better to just use two fields (name, properties) everywhere
otherwise call it eg TestingSystemAccessControlConfiguration

Allow to set custom system access control for tests

nodes.bodyText: No. I don't want to maintain the list. So far it is not needed.
I think I haven't added any new dependency, it is now used explicitly (previously it was transitive). Not much changes.

I wish I could. All I can do right now is to set allow all access control (as it used to be till now), but I am not sure if it is better. TestingPrestoServer requires some non trivial changes to be able to not to require SAC 😞
It requires also properties, I changed that to follow your advice
